commit.message:
Fixed non-conforming identifiers, fixes issue #7

Global identifiers starting with an underscore are reserved, as are identifiers
with adjacent underscores.
Only output language codes containing exactly 3 alphabetic letters; also for COMM frames

Only output valid ISO-639-2 language codes

This does not solve #9 completely as invalid data can still be
printed, but if tags are done properly with id3ted itself, e.g.:

id3ted --USLT "$(< lyrics):description text:eng" the.mp3

"eng" should always be printed without extra bytes from the
TByteVector::data() method.
Define TIMESPEC_TO_TIMEVAL if not defined; fixes issue #8
Fixed old long option in help screen
Fixed frametable binary search, fixes issue #5
Merged CHANGELOG & INSTALL doc files into README.md
Fixed glitches in README between gh-flavour/classic markdown
Tried to fix some markdown glitches in README
Updated README, use markdown for gh-pages creation
Refactored compile-time setting of default encoding
Removed FileIO::_basename, extract apics in files' dir
